body:
Hi @eximius313,

This was a problem with `hibernate-jpamodelgen`. I've noticed that it was generating the following code when using version `5.3.12.Final`:

```java
package model;

import (@javax.validation.constraints.NotNull :: byte);
import java.time.ZonedDateTime;
import javax.annotation.Generated;
import javax.persistence.metamodel.SingularAttribute;
import javax.persistence.metamodel.StaticMetamodel;

@Generated(value = "org.hibernate.jpamodelgen.JPAMetaModelEntityProcessor")
@StaticMetamodel(MyEntity.class)
public abstract class MyEntity_ {

	public static volatile SingularAttribute<MyEntity, NotNull :: byte)[]> data;
	public static volatile SingularAttribute<MyEntity, ZonedDateTime> created;
	public static volatile SingularAttribute<MyEntity, Long> id;

}
```
The code above is not valid Java code as you can see. Updating `hibernate-jpamodelgen` to the [latest version](https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.hibernate/hibernate-jpamodelgen/5.3.6.Final) (`5.3..6.Final`) solved the problem. There is also [HHH-12612](https://hibernate.atlassian.net/browse/HHH-12612) with a discussion and claiming that it is also fixed for version `5.2.18`, but apparently this was not released yet.

But why was it working for 2.6.x?

Probably due to better compatibility between `hibernate-jpamodelgen` and `hibernate-validator` version used by Play 2.6.x ( `5.4.1.Final`). For Play 2.7.0-M3 we are using `hibernate-validator` `6.0.12.Final`. If we force `5.4.1.Final` on your reproducer **without** changing `hibernate-jpamodelgen` it also works:

```scala
dependencyOverrides ++= Seq(
  "org.hibernate" % "hibernate-validator" % "5.4.1.Final"
)
```

Of course, this is not recommended. So better to go with `hibernate-jpamodelgen` update.

Given all that, I'm closing this.
